Smart city designs leverage information and communication technologies to enhance the efficiency, sustainability, and overall quality of urban life. These designs integrate digital innovations to address various challenges faced by cities, such as 
traffic congestion environmental issues, and resource management.

1. Internet of things integration - 
Smart sensors : deploy sensors throughout the city to collect real-time data on traffic, air quality, waste management, and other parameters.
connected devices : integrate devices such as smart streetlights, waste bins, and parking meters to enhance city services.

2. Data analytics and artificial intelligence -
Data-driven decision making - use data analytics to analyze large datasets and derive insights for informed decision-making.
